entor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"3fb9b3c\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-cc88e83\" data-id=\"cc88e83\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8fa06ee elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8fa06ee\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Carotid Body Tumor<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-c564914 elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"c564914\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-0c71250\" data-id=\"0c71250\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6c528b4 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"6c528b4\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Basics<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Also Known As:<ul><li>Carotid Paraganglioma<\/li><li>Carotid Chemodectoma<\/li><li>Glomus Tumor<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Most are Benign &amp; Slow Growing But May Be Locally Aggressive<\/li><li>Most are Nonfunctional \u2013 But Can Potentially Secrete Catecholamines<\/li><li>Highly Vascular<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Forms<\/strong><\/p><ul><li><em>Spontaneous<\/em> \u2013 Most Common<\/li><li><em>Familial<\/em> \u2013 More Frequently Bilateral or Present Earlier<\/li><li><em>Hyperplastic<\/em> \u2013 More Common if Exposed to Prolonged Hypoxia (COPD or Living at High Altitudes)<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Shamblin Classification<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Group I: Small &amp; Easily Dissected Off the Carotid Artery Walls<\/li><li>Group II: Larger, Partially Surround &amp; More Adherent to the Carotid Artery Adventitia<\/li><li>Group III: Encase the Carotid Arteries with Intimate Adherence<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Presentation<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Asymptomatic Neck Mass \u2013 Most Common<\/li><li>\u201cFontaine Sign\u201d (Laterally Mobile but Fixed Longitudinally \u2013 From Association with Artery)<\/li><li>Pain<\/li><li>Compressive Symptoms (Dysphagia, Hoarseness or Horner\u2019s Syndrome)<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Diagnosis<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Dx: US or CTA\/MRA<ul><li>\u201cLyre Sign\u201d Pathognomonic (<strong>Widened Bifurcation &amp; Tumor Blush Between<\/strong>)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Do Not Bx \u2013 Due to Bleeding Risk<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Treatment<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Primary Tx: <strong>Surgical Resection<\/strong><ul><li>Keep to Periadventitial Plane if Able \u2013 Extension of Adventitia May Weaken Artery &amp; Cause Hemorrhage<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Consider Preoperative Angioembolization Prior if Large (&gt; 4 cm)<\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-af8fbb9\" data-id=\"af8fbb9\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c99ddc1 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"c99ddc1\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-12710 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/Carotid-Body-Tumor-Intraop.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"418\" srcset=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/Carotid-Body-Tumor-Intraop.jpg 500w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/Carotid-Body-Tumor-Intraop-300x251.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p><p>Carotid Body Tumor <sup>1<\/sup><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-2efe1da elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"2efe1da\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-12709 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/Carotid-Body-Tumor-CTA.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https:\/